premise_source_doc_sentence: Ranveer Singh Bhavnani  (  born 6 July 1985  )  is an Indian film actor who appears in Hindi films .
After completing a bachelor 's degree from Indiana University Bloomington , Singh returned to India to pursue a career in film .
He made his acting debut in 2010 with a leading role in Yash Raj Films ' romantic comedy Band Baaja Baaraat .
The film emerged as a critical and commercial success , earning Singh a Filmfare Award in the Best Male Debut category .

Singh went on to star in the romantic drama Lootera  (  2013  )  , Sanjay Leela Bhansali 's tragic romance Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela  (  2013  )  , his biggest commercial successes to that point , and in the action-drama Gunday  (  2014  )  .

In 2015 , he starred in the ensemble comedy-drama Dil Dhadakne Do  (  2015  )  , and portrayed Bajirao in Bajirao Mastani , one of the highest-grossing Bollywood films , for which he garnered critical acclaim and won the Filmfare Award for Best Actor .
